{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I am very, very happy to be amidst some of the most --"},{"time":5000,"text":"the lights are really disturbing my eyes"},{"time":7000,"text":"and they're reflecting on my glasses."},{"time":9000,"text":"I am very happy and honored to be amidst"},{"time":13000,"text":"very, very innovative and intelligent people."},{"time":16000,"text":"I have listened to the three previous speakers,"},{"time":19000,"text":"and guess what happened?"},{"time":21000,"text":"Every single thing I planned to say, they have said it here,"},{"time":24000,"text":"and it looks and sounds like I have nothing else to say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":30000,"text":"But there is a saying in my culture"},{"time":33000,"text":"that if a bud leaves a tree without saying something,"},{"time":38000,"text":"that bud is a young one."},{"time":41000,"text":"So, I will -- since I am not young and am very old,"},{"time":46000,"text":"I still will say something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48000,"text":"We are hosting this conference at a very opportune moment,"},{"time":53000,"text":"because another conference is taking place in Berlin."},{"time":55000,"text":"It is the G8 Summit."},{"time":58000,"text":"The G8 Summit proposes that the solution to Africa's problems"},{"time":65000,"text":"should be a massive increase in aid,"},{"time":68000,"text":"something akin to the Marshall Plan."},{"time":70000,"text":"Unfortunately, I personally do not believe in the Marshall Plan."},{"time":74000,"text":"One, because the benefits of the Marshall Plan have been overstated."},{"time":79000,"text":"Its largest recipients were Germany and France,"},{"time":82000,"text":"and it was only 2.5 percent of their GDP."},{"time":85000,"text":"An average African country receives foreign aid"},{"time":88000,"text":"to the tune of 13, 15 percent of its GDP,"},{"time":94000,"text":"and that is an unprecedented transfer of financial resources"},{"time":97000,"text":"from rich countries to poor countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100000,"text":"But I want to say that there are two things we need to connect."},{"time":103000,"text":"How the media covers Africa in the West, and the consequences of that."},{"time":109000,"text":"By displaying despair, helplessness and hopelessness,"},{"time":112000,"text":"the media is telling the truth about Africa, and nothing but the truth."},{"time":118000,"text":"However, the media is not telling us the whole truth."},{"time":122000,"text":"Because despair, civil war, hunger and famine,"},{"time":126000,"text":"although they're part and parcel of our African reality,"},{"time":130000,"text":"they are not the only reality."},{"time":132000,"text":"And secondly, they are the smallest reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134000,"text":"Africa has 53 nations."},{"time":136000,"text":"We have civil wars only in six countries,"},{"time":139000,"text":"which means that the media are covering only six countries."},{"time":143000,"text":"Africa has immense opportunities that never navigate"},{"time":147000,"text":"through the web of despair and helplessness"},{"time":149000,"text":"that the Western media largely presents to its audience."},{"time":154000,"text":"But the effect of that presentation is, it appeals to sympathy."},{"time":158000,"text":"It appeals to pity. It appeals to something called charity."},{"time":163000,"text":"And, as a consequence, the Western view"},{"time":166000,"text":"of Africa's economic dilemma is framed wrongly."},{"time":171000,"text":"The wrong framing is a product of thinking"},{"time":175000,"text":"that Africa is a place of despair."},{"time":178000,"text":"What should we do with it? We should give food to the hungry."},{"time":181000,"text":"We should deliver medicines to those who are ill."},{"time":184000,"text":"We should send peacekeeping troops"},{"time":186000,"text":"to serve those who are facing a civil war."},{"time":188000,"text":"And in the process, Africa has been stripped of self-initiative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193000,"text":"I want to say that it is important to recognize"},{"time":196000,"text":"that Africa has fundamental weaknesses."},{"time":199000,"text":"But equally, it has opportunities and a lot of potential."},{"time":203000,"text":"We need to reframe the challenge that is facing Africa,"},{"time":207000,"text":"from a challenge of despair,"},{"time":209000,"text":"which is called poverty reduction,"},{"time":213000,"text":"to a challenge of hope."},{"time":215000,"text":"We frame it as a challenge of hope, and that is worth creation."},{"time":219000,"text":"The challenge facing all those who are interested in Africa"},{"time":222000,"text":"is not the challenge of reducing poverty."},{"time":224000,"text":"It should be a challenge of creating wealth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227000,"text":"Once we change those two things --"},{"time":230000,"text":"if you say the Africans are poor and they need poverty reduction,"},{"time":235000,"text":"you have the international cartel of good intentions"},{"time":239000,"text":"moving onto the continent, with what?"},{"time":242000,"text":"Medicines for the poor, food relief for those who are hungry,"},{"time":245000,"text":"and peacekeepers for those who are facing civil war."},{"time":250000,"text":"And in the process, none of these things really are productive"},{"time":254000,"text":"because you are treating the symptoms, not the causes"},{"time":256000,"text":"of Africa's fundamental problems."},{"time":259000,"text":"Sending somebody to school and giving them medicines,"},{"time":262000,"text":"ladies and gentlemen, does not create wealth for them."},{"time":267000,"text":"Wealth is a function of income, and income comes from you finding"},{"time":271000,"text":"a profitable trading opportunity or a well-paying job."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275000,"text":"Now, once we begin to talk about wealth creation in Africa,"},{"time":278000,"text":"our second challenge will be,"},{"time":280000,"text":"who are the wealth-creating agents in any society?"},{"time":283000,"text":"They are entrepreneurs. [Unclear] told us they are always"},{"time":287000,"text":"about four percent of the population, but 16 percent are imitators."},{"time":291000,"text":"But they also succeed at the job of entrepreneurship."},{"time":296000,"text":"So, where should we be putting the money?"},{"time":299000,"text":"We need to put money where it can productively grow."},{"time":304000,"text":"Support private investment in Africa, both domestic and foreign."},{"time":308000,"text":"Support research institutions,"},{"time":311000,"text":"because knowledge is an important part of wealth creation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315000,"text":"But what is the international aid community doing with Africa today?"},{"time":319000,"text":"They are throwing large sums of money for primary health,"},{"time":322000,"text":"for primary education, for food relief."},{"time":325000,"text":"The entire continent has been turned into"},{"time":327000,"text":"a place of despair, in need of charity."},{"time":330000,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen, can any one of you tell me"},{"time":332000,"text":"a neighbor, a friend, a relative that you know,"},{"time":335000,"text":"who became rich by receiving charity?"},{"time":339000,"text":"By holding the begging bowl and receiving alms?"},{"time":342000,"text":"Does any one of you in the audience have that person?"},{"time":345000,"text":"Does any one of you know a country that developed because of"},{"time":350000,"text":"the generosity and kindness of another?"},{"time":353000,"text":"Well, since I'm not seeing the hand,"},{"time":355000,"text":"it appears that what I'm stating is true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358000,"text":"(Bono: Yes!)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":360000,"text":"Andrew Mwenda: I can see Bono says he knows the country."},{"time":362000,"text":"Which country is that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":363000,"text":"(Bono: It's an Irish land.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":364000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":366000,"text":"(Bono: [unclear])"}]},{"cues":[{"time":368000,"text":"AM: Thank you very much. But let me tell you this."},{"time":372000,"text":"External actors can only present to you an opportunity."},{"time":376000,"text":"The ability to utilize that opportunity and turn it into an advantage"},{"time":381000,"text":"depends on your internal capacity."},{"time":383000,"text":"Africa has received many opportunities."},{"time":385000,"text":"Many of them we haven't benefited much."},{"time":388000,"text":"Why? Because we lack the internal, institutional framework"},{"time":393000,"text":"and policy framework that can make it possible for us"},{"time":396000,"text":"to benefit from our external relations. I'll give you an example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399000,"text":"Under the Cotonou Agreement,"},{"time":401000,"text":"formerly known as the Lome Convention,"},{"time":404000,"text":"African countries have been given an opportunity by Europe"},{"time":407000,"text":"to export goods, duty-free, to the European Union market."},{"time":412000,"text":"My own country, Uganda, has a quota to export 50,000 metric tons"},{"time":418000,"text":"of sugar to the European Union market."},{"time":421000,"text":"We haven't exported one kilogram yet."},{"time":423000,"text":"We import 50,000 metric tons of sugar from Brazil and Cuba."},{"time":432000,"text":"Secondly, under the beef protocol of that agreement,"},{"time":435000,"text":"African countries that produce beef"},{"time":437000,"text":"have quotas to export beef duty-free to the European Union market."},{"time":442000,"text":"None of those countries, including Africa's most successful nation, Botswana,"},{"time":446000,"text":"has ever met its quota."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449000,"text":"So, I want to argue today that the fundamental source of Africa's"},{"time":454000,"text":"inability to engage the rest of the world"},{"time":456000,"text":"in a more productive relationship"},{"time":459000,"text":"is because it has a poor institutional and policy framework."},{"time":463000,"text":"And all forms of intervention need support,"},{"time":466000,"text":"the evolution of the kinds of institutions that create wealth,"},{"time":470000,"text":"the kinds of institutions that increase productivity."},{"time":473000,"text":"How do we begin to do that, and why is aid the bad instrument?"},{"time":477000,"text":"Aid is the bad instrument, and do you know why?"},{"time":479000,"text":"Because all governments across the world need money to survive."},{"time":483000,"text":"Money is needed for a simple thing like keeping law and order."},{"time":487000,"text":"You have to pay the army and the police to show law and order."},{"time":489000,"text":"And because many of our governments are quite dictatorial,"},{"time":493000,"text":"they need really to have the army clobber the opposition."},{"time":497000,"text":"The second thing you need to do is pay your political hangers-on."},{"time":502000,"text":"Why should people support their government?"},{"time":503000,"text":"Well, because it gives them good, paying jobs,"},{"time":505000,"text":"or, in many African countries, unofficial opportunities"},{"time":509000,"text":"to profit from corruption."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511000,"text":"The fact is no government in the world,"},{"time":514000,"text":"with the exception of a few, like that of Idi Amin,"},{"time":516000,"text":"can seek to depend entirely on force as an instrument of rule."},{"time":521000,"text":"Many countries in the [unclear], they need legitimacy."},{"time":524000,"text":"To get legitimacy, governments often need to deliver things like primary education,"},{"time":530000,"text":"primary health, roads, build hospitals and clinics."},{"time":535000,"text":"If the government's fiscal survival"},{"time":537000,"text":"depends on it having to raise money from its own people,"},{"time":541000,"text":"such a government is driven by self-interest"},{"time":543000,"text":"to govern in a more enlightened fashion."},{"time":545000,"text":"It will sit with those who create wealth."},{"time":548000,"text":"Talk to them about the kind of policies and institutions"},{"time":551000,"text":"that are necessary for them to expand a scale and scope of business"},{"time":555000,"text":"so that it can collect more tax revenues from them."},{"time":558000,"text":"The problem with the African continent"},{"time":560000,"text":"and the problem with the aid industry"},{"time":561000,"text":"is that it has distorted the structure of incentives"},{"time":564000,"text":"facing the governments in Africa."},{"time":567000,"text":"The productive margin in our governments' search for revenue"},{"time":570000,"text":"does not lie in the domestic economy,"},{"time":573000,"text":"it lies with international donors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575000,"text":"Rather than sit with Ugandan --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":577000,"text":"(Applause) --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":581000,"text":"rather than sit with Ugandan entrepreneurs,"},{"time":584000,"text":"Ghanaian businessmen, South African enterprising leaders,"},{"time":590000,"text":"our governments find it more productive"},{"time":593000,"text":"to talk to the IMF and the World Bank."},{"time":596000,"text":"I can tell you, even if you have ten Ph.Ds.,"},{"time":600000,"text":"you can never beat Bill Gates in understanding the computer industry."},{"time":605000,"text":"Why? Because the knowledge that is required for you to understand"},{"time":609000,"text":"the incentives necessary to expand a business --"},{"time":611000,"text":"it requires that you listen to the people, the private sector actors in that industry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617000,"text":"Governments in Africa have therefore been given an opportunity,"},{"time":620000,"text":"by the international community, to avoid building"},{"time":623000,"text":"productive arrangements with your own citizens,"},{"time":625000,"text":"and therefore allowed to begin endless negotiations with the IMF"},{"time":631000,"text":"and the World Bank, and then it is the IMF and the World Bank"},{"time":634000,"text":"that tell them what its citizens need."},{"time":636000,"text":"In the process, we, the African people, have been sidelined"},{"time":640000,"text":"from the policy-making, policy-orientation, and policy-"},{"time":644000,"text":"implementation process in our countries."},{"time":646000,"text":"We have limited input, because he who pays the piper calls the tune."},{"time":650000,"text":"The IMF, the World Bank, and the cartel of good intentions in the world"},{"time":654000,"text":"has taken over our rights as citizens,"},{"time":657000,"text":"and therefore what our governments are doing, because they depend on aid,"},{"time":660000,"text":"is to listen to international creditors rather than their own citizens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664000,"text":"But I want to put a caveat on my argument,"},{"time":666000,"text":"and that caveat is that it is not true that aid is always destructive."},{"time":674000,"text":"Some aid may have built a hospital, fed a hungry village."},{"time":681000,"text":"It may have built a road, and that road"},{"time":683000,"text":"may have served a very good role."},{"time":685000,"text":"The mistake of the international aid industry"},{"time":687000,"text":"is to pick these isolated incidents of success,"},{"time":691000,"text":"generalize them, pour billions and trillions of dollars into them,"},{"time":696000,"text":"and then spread them across the whole world,"},{"time":698000,"text":"ignoring the specific and unique circumstances in a given village,"},{"time":703000,"text":"the skills, the practices, the norms and habits"},{"time":706000,"text":"that allowed that small aid project to succeed --"},{"time":709000,"text":"like in Sauri village, in Kenya, where Jeffrey Sachs is working --"},{"time":712000,"text":"and therefore generalize this experience"},{"time":715000,"text":"as the experience of everybody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":718000,"text":"Aid increases the resources available to governments,"},{"time":723000,"text":"and that makes working in a government the most profitable thing"},{"time":727000,"text":"you can have, as a person in Africa seeking a career."},{"time":730000,"text":"By increasing the political attractiveness of the state,"},{"time":734000,"text":"especially in our ethnically fragmented societies in Africa,"},{"time":738000,"text":"aid tends to accentuate ethnic tensions"},{"time":741000,"text":"as every single ethnic group now begins struggling to enter the state"},{"time":747000,"text":"in order to get access to the foreign aid pie."},{"time":750000,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen, the most enterprising people in Africa"},{"time":755000,"text":"cannot find opportunities to trade and to work in the private sector"},{"time":760000,"text":"because the institutional and policy environment is hostile to business."},{"time":763000,"text":"Governments are not changing it. Why?"},{"time":765000,"text":"Because they don't need to talk to their own citizens."},{"time":770000,"text":"They talk to international donors."},{"time":772000,"text":"So, the most enterprising Africans end up going to work for government,"},{"time":777000,"text":"and that has increased the political tensions in our countries"},{"time":780000,"text":"precisely because we depend on aid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783000,"text":"I also want to say that it is important for us to"},{"time":787000,"text":"note that, over the last 50 years, Africa has been receiving increasing aid"},{"time":791000,"text":"from the international community,"},{"time":793000,"text":"in the form of technical assistance, and financial aid,"},{"time":796000,"text":"and all other forms of aid."},{"time":798000,"text":"Between 1960 and 2003, our continent received 600 billion dollars of aid,"},{"time":808000,"text":"and we are still told that there is a lot of poverty in Africa."},{"time":811000,"text":"Where has all the aid gone?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":814000,"text":"I want to use the example of my own country, called Uganda,"},{"time":818000,"text":"and the kind of structure of incentives that aid has brought there."},{"time":823000,"text":"In the 2006-2007 budget, expected revenue: 2.5 trillion shillings."},{"time":829000,"text":"The expected foreign aid: 1.9 trillion."},{"time":832000,"text":"Uganda's recurrent expenditure -- by recurrent what do I mean?"},{"time":836000,"text":"Hand-to-mouth is 2.6 trillion."},{"time":840000,"text":"Why does the government of Uganda budget spend 110 percent"},{"time":845000,"text":"of its own revenue?"},{"time":846000,"text":"It's because there's somebody there called foreign aid, who contributes for it."},{"time":851000,"text":"But this shows you that the government of Uganda"},{"time":853000,"text":"is not committed to spending its own revenue"},{"time":857000,"text":"to invest in productive investments,"},{"time":859000,"text":"but rather it devotes this revenue"},{"time":861000,"text":"to paying structure of public expenditure."},{"time":865000,"text":"Public administration, which is largely patronage, takes 690 billion."},{"time":870000,"text":"The military, 380 billion."},{"time":872000,"text":"Agriculture, which employs 18 percent of our poverty-stricken citizens,"},{"time":877000,"text":"takes only 18 billion."},{"time":880000,"text":"Trade and industry takes 43 billion."},{"time":884000,"text":"And let me show you, what does public expenditure --"},{"time":888000,"text":"rather, public administration expenditure -- in Uganda constitute?"},{"time":892000,"text":"There you go. 70 cabinet ministers, 114 presidential advisers,"},{"time":898000,"text":"by the way, who never see the president, except on television."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":904000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":909000,"text":"And when they see him physically, it is at public functions like this,"},{"time":914000,"text":"and even there, it is him who advises them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":918000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":920000,"text":"We have 81 units of local government."},{"time":923000,"text":"Each local government is organized like the central government --"},{"time":925000,"text":"a bureaucracy, a cabinet, a parliament,"},{"time":927000,"text":"and so many jobs for the political hangers-on."},{"time":930000,"text":"There were 56, and when our president wanted to"},{"time":933000,"text":"amend the constitution and remove term limits,"},{"time":936000,"text":"he had to create 25 new districts, and now there are 81."},{"time":940000,"text":"Three hundred thirty-three members of parliament."},{"time":942000,"text":"You need Wembley Stadium to host our parliament."},{"time":944000,"text":"One hundred thirty-four commissions"},{"time":946000,"text":"and semi-autonomous government bodies,"},{"time":951000,"text":"all of which have directors and the cars. And the final thing,"},{"time":955000,"text":"this is addressed to Mr. Bono. In his work, he may help us on this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":959000,"text":"A recent government of Uganda study found"},{"time":961000,"text":"that there are 3,000 four-wheel drive motor vehicles"},{"time":965000,"text":"at the Minister of Health headquarters."},{"time":967000,"text":"Uganda has 961 sub-counties, each of them with a dispensary,"},{"time":972000,"text":"none of which has an ambulance."},{"time":974000,"text":"So, the four-wheel drive vehicles at the headquarters"},{"time":977000,"text":"drive the ministers, the permanent secretaries, the bureaucrats"},{"time":980000,"text":"and the international aid bureaucrats who work in aid projects,"},{"time":983000,"text":"while the poor die without ambulances and medicine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":989000,"text":"Finally, I want to say that before I came to speak here,"},{"time":993000,"text":"I was told that the principle of TEDGlobal"},{"time":997000,"text":"is that the good speech should be like a miniskirt."},{"time":1000000,"text":"It should be short enough to arouse interest,"},{"time":1002000,"text":"but long enough to cover the subject."},{"time":1004000,"text":"I hope I have achieved that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1005000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1006000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1007000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}